Took Number 1
sigcheck it is tool for check the file version number,timestamp,digital signature details 
also there is options to check the file status on Virustotal 

use case check for unsigned file 
C:> sigcheck -u -e C:\Windows\System32
   -u --> show the files that unkown to thw virus total 
   -e --> scan only exeutable files .exe .msi ...
   
Tool Number 2
streams to check for ADS alernative data streams 
use case --> streams <path to file > -accepteula 

or using power shell -->Get-Item C:\Users\Administrator\Desktop\file.txt -stream *
open the file in the ads --> notepad ./file.txt:ads.txt or 
remove the ads file   Clear-Content .\Desktop\file.txt -stream ads.txt

Tool Number 3
SDelete SDelete is a command line utility that takes a number of options. In any given use, 
it allows you to delete one or more files and/or directories, or to cleanse the free space on a logical disk
